Given the roots of two binary trees p and q, write a function to check if they are the same or not.

Two binary trees are considered the same if they are structurally identical, and the nodes have the same value.


class Solution 
{
    public boolean isSameTree(TreeNode p, TreeNode q) 
    {
        if (p==null && q==null)        // Case 1: both are null
        {
            return true;
        }
        if (p==null || q==null)         // Case 2: one is null, the other isn't
        {
            return false;
        }
        if (p.val != q.val)            // Case 3: values differ
        {
            return false;
        }
        return isSameTree(p.left, q.left) && isSameTree(p.right, q.right);        // Case 4: check left and right subtrees
    }
}
